remixlab.bias.branch

Class Branch<E extends Enum<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • remixlab.bias.branch.Branch<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - 'Reference' enum action set.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Copyable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    KeyboardBranch, MotionBranch

    public class Branch<E extends Enum<E>>
extends Object
implements Copyable
    A Branch handles a list of GenericGrabber objects (grabbers(), implementing the same reference action set used to parameterize it. A branch, in turn, is handled by the agent to which it is appended, see: GenericMotionAgent.appendBranch(String) and GenericKeyboardAgent.appendBranch(String). Branches are used by agents to parse a BogusEvent into an GenericGrabber object Action (see handle(GenericGrabber, BogusEvent)).

    To add/remove an GenericGrabber object to/from a Branch, use addGrabber(GenericGrabber) and removeGrabber(Grabber)), respectively. The same operations may be performed directly from the agent (to which the branch is appended): GenericAgent.addGrabber(GenericGrabber, Branch) and Agent.removeGrabber(Grabber).

    Observation: to parse bogus-events branches internally use some Profiles (see profiles()). For instance, the MotionBranch has a MotionBranch.motionProfile() and a MotionBranch.clickProfile()) to be able to parse MotionEvents and ClickEvents, resp. Similarly, to parse KeyboardEvents, a KeyboardBranch uses a KeyboardBranch.keyboardProfile().
